text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
have you ever stayed quiet in a situation where you knew something wasnâ€™t right?
.
i know i have. iâ€™m not proud of it, but my past doesnâ€™t define who i am presently or even in the future. i saw a film tonight called â€œthis changes everything.â€ it was about gender inequality in the film and media industry. but gender inequality goes beyond just that industry. iâ€™ve experienced it in my life. in college i had something happen to me that iâ€™m ashamed of, but needs to be spoken. being a lady farmer is challenging as well. i grew up feeling like i had to have â€œthe bodyâ€ to get anywhere or to have certain friends/boyfriends. i even felt like i wasnâ€™t good enough to do what i wanted to do because of my size, and the fact that i was a lady. but this ends now.
.
i want to be influential, i want to inspire others to follow their passions no matter what gender, race, age, soul is.. i want to show people that no matter the obstacles, we can follow and achieve our dreams. letâ€™s create a world where we stand up for one another, live in equality, and support each otherâ€™s endeavors. weâ€™re all humans, all souls here to live our highest excitement. iâ€™m here for you. will you join me?
.
.

text:
this morningâ€™s run was a shorter version of yesterdayâ€™s. the sleeping dog that made me turn back yesterday was still sleeping in the same spot. if heâ€™s still there on wednesday, it may be because heâ€™s dead. either way, iâ€™ll be letting sleeping dogs lie. iâ€™m also hoping that the man who took his willy out of his pants and worked it shamelessly while staring at me will not be around again. itâ€™s not the first time this has happened but i can always hope itâ€™s the last. there were plenty of people about - he was using a concrete pillar for cover - so it wasnâ€™t scary like the last time but it was a repulsive reminder about the risks for women of running alone. with two daughters on the cusp of adulthood, one flying alone from australia to london as i write, this was a helpful reminder about the need to keep discussing with them the necessity to be always vigilant and risk averse when it comes to personal safety. run safe ladies.

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

thatâ€™s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him â€œwe can take it.â€ no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but itâ€™s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then itâ€™s easy to come along for the ride. thereâ€™s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. theyâ€™re both just characters on the television.

thatâ€™s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. itâ€™s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. itâ€™s that weâ€™ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text: moving to meet the family has not been so great. could blame a lot of things, the timeline for the country, the fact that i spoke up on abuse and topics noone wanted to hear, our very different backgrounds. instead, i just want to say, it sucks having no-one in the remote area to turn to, not only that, moving to a wealthier area, was well, not a good thing to embark on while having no support. i support myself. have always done my best to, had hope and faith in fellow humans at one point dispite all that happened. i don't feel that so much today. supporting myself at another price point in the country there was more togetherness. more relatableness in seeing the despair in each others eyes, no matter who you are. not playing games to make it worse. life has turned out to, kinda just be suffering at the will of my peers born into priveledged lives, and i'll keep working and struggling to maintain and grow, although, it's difficult to acknowledge how self absorbed they are to not even have noticed. also, where does that get you? what are you so mad for? that i worked my way here, and you were born into everything and were standing in the same place? you'll never undo the hurt and effect on the lives you think you're better than, and there's a huge shark pool above your head that'll never welcome you as you never welcome us, capitalism is wrong, and neverending. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors

text_retweet: reposted from @indiaarie -  take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasnâ€™t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke, and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary, i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry, i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed, because it was a graphic illustration, that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesnâ€™t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i donâ€™t need to sing about the fight , my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today, iâ€™m hopeful, that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but, i wont be satisfied until every abused person knows, that â€œeveryone of us is worthyâ€ and when ever someone treats us as less, that is thier mistake, ... and while the wound is not our doing, it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum, when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more, to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo - #regrann

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i tried for so long to get away from who i am. iâ€™ve attempted to change my name on several occasions not finding one that fits. and iâ€™ve decided i am who i am. i am a author, mother, motivational speaker and pushing toward being a activist for us women! and i am also jai love who now realizes i donâ€™t have to stop being who i was born to be just to change and grow! i can be whoever i want to be! ladies hear me! weâ€™ve been silent for too long. weâ€™ve been pushed to the side for too long. so iâ€™ve decided iâ€™m just gonna be me. and stop giving a flying fuck about what the next person thinks about it. iâ€™m out here on a mission, to save women whoâ€™ve been broken hearted like me, whoâ€™ve loved and lost like me, whoâ€™ve been molested like me, whoâ€™ve been abused like me, whoâ€™ve dealt with domestic violence  like me, iâ€™m here saying iâ€™ve been hurt too! and i love you sis!  for everytime you wake up and push forward. for everytime you chose yourself over talking his phone call. for everytime you said i dont think im enough but later on found out you were and always have been! for everytime someone tried to manipulate you through your insecurities! im saying now! you deserve better sista! 
stand with me in reclaiming our beauty, sass, goals, courage, bravery, light and love for self back! 
letâ€™s be stronger than our circumstances! 
#periodt #period #strongertogether #metoo

text:
there is a lot of oblivion and overlooking in the punjabi community when it comes to subjects like sex, sexual abuse and mental health.
itâ€™s sad how unequipped our systems are to provide resources, guidance, and support  that survivors need. itâ€™s hard to be a survivor in a community with so many unacknowledged social issues. i didnâ€™t speak up about the childhood abuse until 9 years later, and i was given the space to speak for about 2 seconds. the system in our culture allows nothing but victim blaming, shaming, and silencing. i keep wondering how can we change this oppressive system? how can we change how we engage in conversations about issues that oppress us? i donâ€™t have all the answers. iâ€™m not entirely ready to come out with my story, and share my life in that light. but iâ€™m trying to speak as much as i can. as much as my soul is ready.  because while speaking about my trauma is so difficult, not speaking about the bullshit some punjabi men are is soul wrenching. so in whatever capacity i can iâ€™m speaking. and if youâ€™re a young punjabi person please talk to your friends, cousins, and siblings about these very very integral and important aspects of our lives. let each other know youâ€™re loved, heard and seen. let no child or friend ever become a victim. build a community so strong no abuser uncle can stand tall. to all my survivors vocal or silent, raged or numb, breaking or healing- i hear you. i love you. and there is nothing you canâ€™t rebuild, and carry powerfully than your own healing. 
take your time. â¤ï¸

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
under the spirit of #metoo, we highlighted the case of sexual violence that is still prevalent in today's society, particularly towards girls and women. with that in mind, almost unanimously, we understood the importance of consent in sexual activities.

but, is consent enough? in 2018 we saw worrying trend of misusing the concept of consent in dealing with sexual violence cases. almost exactly one year ago, we witnessed the entire aziz ansari fiasco with an anonymous woman's account accusing him of sexual violence. in ansari's defense, the act had been consensual. late 2018, irish feminists went enraged as a rape victim's underwear was produced in court as a proof that she'd consented to the harm done to her. of course, we haven't even delved further into the case of agni from ugm and the fact that there are still people who believe that she somewhat must have wanted it.

it is timely that now we have an open discussion about what consent is and more importantly, what it is not. surely, it is not a justification for rape. let's discuss further in our event below:

topic: beyond consent
date: saturday, 12 january 2019
venue: @kenobispace â€” gedung colony kemang, lt. 6

movie: fat girl (2001)

schedule:
18.30 - 18.45: teaser of "invisible hopes" and q & a with director tiar simorangkir
18.45 - 20.15: movie screening
20.15 - 21.45: discussion with vivi widyawati (perempuan mahardhika) and anastasia sijabat (jakarta cinema club)

ticket: 30k

warning: the film is rated r and includes some rape and gore scenes.

discussion will be held in bahasa indonesia.

online ticket can be purchased at livelife:
http://bit.ly/sf120119

text:
a love letter to survivors in 3pts 
featuring @taranajaneen 
pt. 1 - when the memories surface

after finishing #survivingrkelly, i cried several times.
.
the child in me who was hurt and confused by someone i trusted cried
.
the 23,24,&25 yr old versions of myself who were in and out of a sexually, emotionally, and financially abusive relationship cried.
.
i cried for the people on both sides of my family who have been harmed by and have harmed people we love.
.
i cried recalling the intergenerational stories of deep seeded abuse and violence that were told in quiet. violence that persisted in silence and begat more violence. i cried.

i mostly move through my days with painful memories that lie dormant until i come across certain people, places, and/or things. last october, i had the privilege of meeting @taranajaneen. she was presenting an award in recognition of alyssa milanoâ€™s work in the #metoo movement, and afterwards @vnicole11 encouraged me to come with her for a photo. i was nervous to approach her, what would i say? what words could clearly express how grateful i am for her work, her courage, her love? so, i decided that i would stay quiet and just be there in support of my dear friend asking for a photo. i was beyond surprised when she turned around, touched my hand and said â€œsis, i know you. where do i know you from?â€. i literally lost all my words and immediately burst into tears. tears from a place of peace bc i had never felt so deeply seen. i felt like in a split second she saw me and all of the memories i carry of my own experiences and the experiences of my family. i was stunned by this deeply spiritually moment.

to all my fellow survivors, i want you to know that i see you and i love you. i pray that when youâ€™re memories surface, you experience the love and connection i felt in this moment with tarana.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
sexual abuse or any type of abuse is not a joking matter, and this is something i think a lot of families sweep under the rug (more often than not), most families are good at keeping those skeletons locked up. 
i was sexually abused by my grandfather from ages 7 to 11, as i got older i honestly believed that a lot of my family knew what was happening but no one ever spoke up and some were probably monetarily compensated to keep their mouth closed.

one day an older cousin walked in and seen him touching me inappropriately, 2 days later while i was at school (5th grade), i remember seeing two police officers and my teacher walking towards the playground, they escorted me to the nurses office,  where they asked me countless questions and 3 hours later i was placed in foster care. i was a foster child from age 11  to 18, for years i always thought i did something wrong,  he would threaten me,  he would tell me if i didn't do something or if i ever told someone i would be punished. 
i've shared my story with so many, and i thank my cousin for witnessing this and speaking up on my behalf. men and women who prey on children,  the weak and the vulnerable are sick and need some serious help. (there is a special place in hell for all of you). if i've offended anyone in any of my previous post i truly apologize, i am in no way condoning this type of behavior, i have daughters, nieces, cousins,  friends, and i wouldn't wish this on anyone. i have friends who were in abusive relationships, they have shared their stories with me, and a lot of us are so quick to say, "they probably deserved it", it's sad and it's very heartbreaking, especially when this person can be very close to you,  you may see them every day and will never know what's going on behind closed doors. pay attention to those around you,  look for unusual behavior, ask questions, don't allow others to have you in fear, speak up, you were given a voice for a reason. #ninobrown #survivingrkelly #rkelly #metoo #survivor #strength #childabuse #sexualabuse #stopchildabuse

(there is a special place in hell for all of you). if i have offended anyone in any of my previous post i truly apologize, i am in no way condoning this type of behavior, i have daughters, nieces, cousins,  friends, and i would not wish this on anyone. i have friends who were in abusive relationships, they have shared their stories with me, and a lot of us are so quick to say, "they probably deserved it", it is sad and it is very heabreaking, especially when this person can be very close to you,  you may see them every day and will never know what's going on behind closed doors. pay attention to those around you,  look for unusual behavior, ask questions, do not allow others to have you in fear, speak up, you were given a voice for a reason.

text:
these past few years my life has changed in ways i have never dreamed possible.

i finally took the time to pause, to stop running and sit with myself and who it is that i want to be.

i have been known in the past to run to the next venture or the new idea, to distract myself from the pain i was feeling inside.  i was always on the search for a quick fix, that never came and left me even more broken then the time before.

but i decided to change this two years ago.  i knew the direction i wanted to move towards, but forced myself to sit with it for over a year.  i needed to process, find the authenticity in what it was that i wanted to do and share.

i started teacher training, because i wanted to share my experiences with anxiety and depression in hopes to reach other people, to create a safe community where we can grow and explore together.

and today we did just that.

my heart is full, my eyes filled with happy tears.  we came together today as a collective, to feel a little less alone and a little less afraid.  this is what community, support and love look like and i am honored to offer two more weekends of this blessing.

much, much love.
xoxo

text:
watching the surviving r kelly series brought up a lot of emotion for me, it was a harsh reminder of the unhealthy cycle our community continues to feed when we choose to ignore signs of abuse in our circles, families and sometimes in our very own homes. 
we are responsible for each other!

if a family member comes to you and confides in you something that happened to them at the hand of someone you may love  or idolize, please please believe the victim and then support them to do something about it!

it does not matter if it is your dad, brother, aunty or uncle! wrong is wrong! we have a disgusting habit as humans to put the oath of â€œfamily over everythingâ€ but if your family member is abusive and unhealthy then what good is it to protect someone who is ill. 
letâ€™s cut the silence and the pretentiousness for 2019 please!

#timesup #survivingrkelly #torontoblogger #metoo .

take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasnâ€™t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke, and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary, i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry, i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed, because it was a graphic illustration, that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesnâ€™t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i donâ€™t need to sing about the fight , my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today, iâ€™m hopeful, that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but, i wont be satisfied until every abused person knows, that â€œeveryone of us is worthyâ€ and when ever someone treats us as less, that is thier mistake, ... and while the wound is not our doing, it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum, when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more, to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo

i knew something was fucked up about the "age ain't nothing but a number" type shit (but i still tried to use that line to get an older girlfriend, it was in jest and didn't work obviously). this dude was on the scope for years for #pedophilia, #misogyny and a goddamn sex tape (that became a fucking meme after #davechappelle parodied it) and people still decided that kelly's talent and success was much more important than the innocence of young girls.

in my opinion, this whole #fastgirls excuse is the worst way to try to justify him because men can say no, too (would you look at that, i just typed it). austin powers turned down drunk sex. some men out there wait until marriage.

stop blaming girls for this shit. #dobetter

just because you a fan don't mean you know this dude and even if you did, you want to help him, send him some therapy (you know the rest of that rant from #theboondocks )

 become the strong god fearing woman i am today. i heard their stories, and i tried to empower them to let go of their past hurts as we wrote our pain on balloons and released them into the sky. i pray my triumph over my pain gave them hope to never give up!! there is a light at the end of the tunnel, and his name is jesus!!!

text: take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasnâ€™t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke, and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary, i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry, i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed, because it was a graphic illustration, that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesnâ€™t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i donâ€™t need to sing about the fight , my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today, iâ€™m hopeful, that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but, i wont be satisfied until every #survivor know, that â€œeveryone of us is worthyâ€ and when ever someone treats us as less, that is thier mistake, ... and while the wound is not our doing, it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum, when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more, to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo

text:
actress @iamsandraohinsta hosted the 2019 golden globe awards on sunday night â€” and took home an award of her own. oh won best lead actress in a television drama for her role in â€œkilling eve,â€ which was her second golden globes nomination and second win. accepting the award, oh thanked her mother and father, who were in attendance, in both english and korean.
â€¢ 
ahead of the show, oh had said she wanted to bring a lighter tone to the @goldenglobes after last yearâ€™s award show took a much more serious approach and centered on the #metoo movement. she arrived at the red carpet in a classic hollywood bob and white gown with an asymmetrical neckline â€” a contrast to the black dresses worn last year to signify solidarity with #metoo. oh said thursday that she and fellow host @andysamberg will provide a â€œmoment of joyâ€ at the award show sunday night. â€œi know when andy and i were talking about the feeling that i really want to bring, and really focus on, is just to have a moment of joy,â€ said oh, who is favored to win a golden globe award for best actress for her @killingeve role. â€œhonestly, with who is going to be in that audience, the nominees this year, it excites me so tremendously ... mostly because of the diversity in that room.â€ (photo by valerie macon / afp / getty)

we watched all 6 parts of #survivingrkelly and recommend it as a teaching tool for parents to use with teens, not just around issues of sexual assault, abusive relationships, and consent, but also for the ways in which black girls and women are harmed by individuals, institutions, and systems. that being said, we understand if watching it is not possible for those who have experienced sexual abuse and trauma. safety & healing is more important.
.
.
thank you to the survivors and families for telling your stories. thank you to #dreamhampton for creating space for black girls and women to be heard. thank you @taranajaneen for continuing to center black girls and women in conversations around sexual assault. we have linked the @colorofchange petition for @rcarecords to drop r. kelly in our stories.
.
.
the website blackwomentoo.com is also linked in our profile. "it was created by and for black women and alliesâ€”and visualizes the systems that put our minds and bodies at risk." there are pages on black girlhood, college and university campuses, employment, entertainment industry, healthcare, housing, law enforcement, legal system, media, and policy makers. everyone should visit this website to see and understand all the ways our systems and institutions fail black girls and women. no more allowing black women to be the only ones showing up and speaking out on these issues.

text:
"find out who you are and do it on purpose." - #dollyparton #dumplin

today, i was babying my daughter and i asked, "who loves you!" to my surprise, she said, "me! i love me!" **
and it hit me -- wow. when we get asked what things/ people we love, when do we ever mention ourselves? why do we make out the idea of being 'so full of ourselves' a bad thing? who's going to fill us up if we don't?
**
as i stand in the present, i am breathing in the bigger plan for all my past struggles, challenges and disappointments. all the years i felt so ugly, unworthy, inadequate and anxious were just stitches in the tapestry. when i look back, i see that jesus was always on my side and it makes me overwhelmingly grateful. because of this spiritual awakening, i'm kinder to myself and more forgiving and compassionate. you have to look in the mirror and love yourself, woman. you have to live in your own skin and let your energy shine. be loyal to her. protect her. hug her. love her. when you do that, can't nobody tell you nothin! ğŸ’–ğŸŒ» #faith #love #hope #trust #joy #masterpiece #expression #mystory #metoo #healing #journey #empowerment #author #storyteller #worthy #godlywoman

text:
unconditional parenting
parenting is by far the most difficult job in the world as you constantly have to balance between responsibility, discipline, generosity and love... you are a model, a point of reference, security, strength and at the same time you provide love, attention and support unconditionally.
i always say that you make children for them not for you because you help them grow, you teach them how to embrace life and its challenges, how to become themselves and be fulfilled. you let them be with guidance and wisdom. .
.
.

text:
to the person who recently told me to build a bridge and get over it, that everyone has had a hard life.you will not minimalize my story. the path, the road i have travelled has made me who i am today and if you canâ€™t see me as i am or even the beauty in that story then thatâ€™s a lacking in you; not me. see iâ€™m the woman whoâ€™s grown from a childhood filled with sexual abuse. a 14 year old homeless runaway due to that abuse. a child who was manipulated, mentally abused and raped because her voice was taken. iâ€™m the 14 year old whoâ€™s being told sheâ€™s a hypochondriac and isnâ€™t really sick. iâ€™m that same girl being diagnosed with crohns and is all alone. iâ€™m the 18 year old that became a topless barmaid to steal back any kinda power she could find. the power that is a twisted therapy session behind a giant bar with me dictating the rules. who wasnâ€™t doing it for drugs or sleeping around but for any resemblance of ownership of her body and voice. iâ€™m the girl who so desperately wanted to be loved by a father figure due to her own toxic non existent father. 
iâ€™m the girl who lay there silently because she was so beaten down mentally she just wanted to be loved. iâ€™m the 21 year old woman who was approached by her abuser like nothing had happened (as he did so many times) and heard him verbally assault me all over again. but iâ€™m also the 21 year old woman who finally stole her voice back and stood up for herself for the first time in her life. iâ€™m the woman who claimed back her worth and power slowly through small singular steps. through seeing, listening and being. iâ€™m the woman who lived in greece and the uk with no help from anyone. i travelled and grew and learnt. iâ€™m the woman who fell pregnant unexpectedly but who embraced the life and the future ahead of me openly. iâ€™m the 27 year old with a 6mth old baby and a partner who doesnâ€™t want to see whatâ€™s in front of him - a dying woman fading away. iâ€™m the woman who has been silenced, manipulated and bullied by medical professionals. who almost died multiple times all while trying to just hold my new baby. iâ€™m also the woman who now knows her worth. who knows who she is. 
continued in comments or fb post....

text:
on new year's eve, we opened our apartment to loved ones for a vision board party. and what a blast we had. (never heard of a vision board? it's a board filled with words and pictures, used to visually stimulate you to achieve your goals for the year. stay tuned for a how-to video next week.) beside this party animal are treasured mentors of my husband and i. these old folk have really been a blessing to me and marriage. 
if you haven't already found mentors/older mature christians, pray and ask god to lead them to you or approach whoever god lays on your heart.

there're so many things about myself that i wouldn't have been able to see without these two in the lives of me and my husband. 
you never know how godly mentors in your impact your life. go for it.

do you have any awesome accountability partners or mentors? shout them out in the comment section below. ğŸ˜‰

this week, a six-part documentary on lifetime is taking an expansive look at the allegations against mr. kelly, a chart-topping artist whose history has invited extra scrutiny in recent years.

the series, â€œsurviving r. kelly,â€ includes testimony from several women who accuse the singer of abuse, as well as commentary from mr. kellyâ€™s critics, including the founder of the #metoo movement, tarana burke, and the singer john legend.

the six episodes, each an hour long, cover the long history of allegations against mr. kelly. they feature women who described being controlled or abused by him, often when they were teenagers, as well as associates and relatives of the singer

text:

join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar (link in bio) where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! ***
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!!!! #motivation #empoweringwomen #2019 #indianapolis #newyeargoal

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

'surviving r. kelly' documentary features victims of the singer as they share harrowing details of sex abuse for over 20 years, r. kelly has been accused by multiple women of sexual misconduct and abuse but he has so far denied all the allegations.this week, a documentary produced by lifetime is exploring the allegations brought against robert kelly.multiple alleged victims of the singer, including his ex-wife andrea kelly all featured in the documentary and they spoke about their ordeal.as expected, a lot of tears were shed as the women recounted the alleged abuse - sexual, mental, emotional, and physical - which they suffered in the hands of r. kelly.Â Â the documentary, made up of six parts,Â includes commentary from r. kellyâ€™s critics, including the founder of the #metoo movement, tarana burke, and the singer john legend.the docu-series has gained attention and is being widely debated on social media, with a lot of people saying the singer has escaped the consequences of his actions for far too long. there were also those who came to the defence of the singer.below are previews of the docu-series which began showing from january 4 to jan 6.Â Â donâ€™t miss the powerful conclusion of the series that has everyone talking. the finale of #survivingrkelly premieres tonight at 9/8c. . . . . . #rkelly #docuseries #lifetime #tv #documentarya post shared by lifetime tv (@lifetimetv) on jan 5, 2019 at 4:27pm pstÂ Â tune-in to the final night of the #survivingrkelly special tonight at 9/8c. . . . . . #rkelly #docuseries #lifetime #tv #documentarya post shared by lifetime tv (@lifetimetv) on jan 5, 2019 at 3:05pm pst Â the post 'surviving r. kelly' documentary features victims of the singer as they share harrowing details of sex abuse appeared first on linda ikeji blog.

text:
women will always be caring, nurturing, loving, sharing and loyal. after watching surviving r.kelly, on @lifetimetv i started reflecting on how black women were used by men (from all races really), oversexualized, misunderstood, disrespected and broken because we are thought of as ikea furniture. from as long as i can remember, black women were said to be â€œdisrespectful, big mouthed and untamableâ€ when really we would always defend our men even when they did us wrong. but whoâ€™s protecting us? nobody! 
everyone failed those lil girls, every single one of us. the parents for pimping their child for a check, the industry for turning a blind eye, the justice system for letting him go, black folks for supporting him by stepping in the name of love! by doing that we only gave him strength to do whatever afterwards but whoâ€™s behind to pick up these women? whoâ€™s behind to pick us up?
that brought me to a moment when somebody i know told be me about a girlâ€™s story, he was not supposed to mess with her emotionally but when i asked him why (she is a petite white woman, nothing against her) but he said something like â€œi donâ€™t want to hurt her because sheâ€™s been through a lot, she is fragileâ€ and i looked at that person perplexed like â€œwhat? what about your gfâ€ (gf who happens to be black and more statuesque) and he was like â€œi know sheâ€™s been hurt before but she is strong and she does not need my helpâ€ (something to that extent). and that bothered me and my spirit because all i could think watching the r.kelly abuse story, my story, this girlâ€™s story, black women stories is that regardless of how bad we hurt we can be by life experiences, people will always perceive us as being too fast, too sexy, too independent, too loud or tough enough to handle everything. 
bottom line is : a black woman is just resilient enough to stand on her own, caring enough to protect your honor and forgiving

text:
#metoo, but also #youtoo 
in the last year, iâ€™ve done so much work around sexual assault and domestic violence and the biggest thing iâ€™ve learned is that i think we need to strongly caution ourselves about creating a false narrative for the me too movement. 
tarana burke reminds us: â€œthis is not a movement about taking down powerful men. it's not even a woman's movement. it's a movement for survivors." if we lose the fact that this movement is for survivors, we have lose the power to change ourselves. itâ€™s so easy to focus our anger on the system we believe is hurting us. we want to generalize and say itâ€™s because we live in a patriarchal system, but that is leading men to get targeted in ways they never should. 
if this was solely just about patriarchy men would not be being sexually abused as well. itâ€™s about more than that, itâ€™s about the abuse and misuse of power. 
a few weeks ago i sat down with a male friend who shared his â€œme tooâ€ moment with me. we were sitting there and he turned and said to me â€œyou know casey, i didnâ€™t know that about you until you shared your story, but that happened to me too.â€ over the last year, iâ€™ve held so many stories like this for strong men who havenâ€™t ever spoken up.  they are survivors as well. 
letâ€™s come together and listen to each other across all divisions. 
#metoo #youtoo #domesticviolence #fighter #fightback #voice #gender #women #men #empathy #vulnerability #survivor #ownit

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

cnn

text:
4 years later. moving day. i'd lie if i said i was happy or ecstatic. i feel like life was stagnant since the death of my mom in 2014. i lost my job, lost my condo....then went through hell with my boyfriend who was struggling with addiction. now hes employed and functional.  also during these years i struggled with severe depression and attempted suicide twice. had a very close 'friend' steal my savings. never got back the 12k she stole. our justice system is so fucked up. she killed my credit.  absolutely destroyed it. also had a friends husband sexually assault me. again our justice system didnt give a fuck. 
i have been holding my breath for what seems like my entire life...and i prob have. what happened in these last 4 years was kinda representative of my life. i have always been a victim of someone else's misplaced rage or sexual depravity. i have lived a life a victim of abuse 
i hope this move allows me to finally live a life i wanted to live shortly after my moms passing but due to having other people take turns at destroying my life. i want to be selfish....i want to enjoy life. i want my life to be a reflection of my mom and dad who both passed away too soon. #fuckcancer

in truth, i am scared. i only know how to live in fear. i dont know what it takes to want to live. i just know survival. this is a bit much but i'm not hiding anymore. time for me to truly live and have my voice heard. my story continues and needs to be expressed
#movingday #nursesofinstagram #survivors #metoo #2019 #newlife #newbeginnings #stressedaf #liveoutloud #sexualassaultsurvivor #hope #life #love #live #fear #myvoice #mystorycontinues #depression #bipolarstruggles #grief #createyourdestiny #spiritualgrowth #mentalhealthawareness

text:
jazz and gender:
finding solidarity 
toshi reagon, roxy coss, vanessa reed, maria grand, fay victor, john murph, and co-moderated by sarah elizabeth charles and nate chinen

sunday january 6th - 2:00pm

the assemblage, 17 john street nyc

all ages

the issues around sexual harassment, discrimination and gender bias in jazz have been a focus of conversation in recent years, taking on additional momentum in the #metoo era. winter jazzfest supports the keychange initiative, which seeks to achieve gender balance in festival programming, and has engaged with these ideas in previous panels. this one poses a pressing question: what does it mean to be an ally in the jazz community, at this point in time? co-moderated by vocalist sarah elizabeth charles and critic nate chinen, the panel will include artist representatives from the we have voice collective and the women in jazz organization, keychange founder vanessa reed â€” as well as musicians seeking to further develop and exist as allies in the conversation around gender relations and identify

tw: rape/sexual assault
â€œcaressed by your lover in the dead of night 
tears tumble. 
your lover is puzzled, 
you, embarrassed. 
even with years passed 
you
still feel foreign in your own body, like a tenant paying a debt to the thieves 
who stole peace off of your nightstand. *
some play devils advocate like a drinking game. 
for the hell of it they will force you to see the grey in the black and white of your trauma. 
some donâ€™t believe you.
sometimes you donâ€™t believe you. *
so you do the therapy and the face masks and the new haircut.
you did the journal entry but still the scent of burnt cigarettes and sweat makes your heart race. 
see i like you know what it is like when a devil finds their home inside you and even with eviction notices of sage and tears and screams into your pillow you still wear 
label victim 
label survivor 
label rape victim/survivor like a cattle brand you got while sleeping. 
but
i believe you. 
i hear you. 
i see you. 
if it was yesterday or 100 years ago. 
i believe you.
i hear you.
i see you.
no matter who they were. their accolades or medals. their gender or race or religion. their tax bracket or good deeds. if they are your family or an ex lover.
i believe you. 
i hear you. 
i see you. 
and that will never change. 
come find rest in my weary arms. come,
letâ€™s find peace
for our nightstand
and water for our garden. â€œ

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
have you been taught math the chocolate way? "if tommy has a chocolate and divides it into 4 and gives 2 pieces to his friends, how many pieces does he have left?"
i think most of us were taught this way. and it's not just math. this is the foundation we build our understanding of the world on. if someone has something, there's less of it for us to have. 
but it doesn't always work like that. we're not tommy and the chocolate here. we're five loaves and two fishes. what is cast into the universe will multiply.
one woman who raises her voice in the #metoo gives strength to 10 others around her to speak up. the more courage there is, the more courage there will be.
one person who has created great art will move a dozen others who see it to create great art too. the more inspiration and authenticity there is, the more inspiration and authenticity there will be.
so don't worry that someone else is going to do what you could have done or take away what you could have had. no one can walk your path. 
in fact, you should probably rejoice when you see the person next to you succeed because they've put out more success and joy into the universe for you to have. just something to think about next time.
.
.
.
.

text:
kogan maintains that everything he did was legal and he had a â€œclose working relationshipâ€ with facebook, which had granted him permission for his apps.

cambridge analytica had its data. this was the foundation of everything it did next â€“ how it extracted psychological insights from the â€œseedersâ€ and then built an algorithm to profile millions more.

for more than a year, the reporting around what cambridge analytica did or didnâ€™t do for trump has revolved around the question of â€œpsychographicsâ€, but wylie points out: â€œeverything was built on the back of that data. the models, the algorithm. everything. why wouldnâ€™t you use it in your biggest campaign ever?â€ in december 2015, the guardianâ€™s harry davies published the first report about cambridge analytica acquiring facebook data and using it to support ted cruz in his campaign to be the us republican candidate. but it wasnâ€™t until many months later that facebook took action. and then, all they did was write a letter. in august 2016, shortly before the us election, and two years after the breach took place, facebookâ€™s lawyers wrote to wylie, who left cambridge analytica in 2014, and told him the data had been illicitly obtained and that â€œgsr was not authorised to share or sell itâ€. they said it must be deleted immediately.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text_retweet:
ever since #sexual #assault allegations against #hollywood producer harvey weinstein came to light last year, the #metoo movement â€” initially launched over a decade ago by activist tarana burke â€” has prompted millions of #survivors around the world to come forward and share their own stories. moreover, after #actress alyssa milano's #metoo tweet went viral in october 2017, #metoo has caused #google searches about sexual assault to shatter records and reach an all-time high.
.
.
last october, #the newyork times broke the news that #weinstein had faced numerous sexual assault allegations over the years, and that he had paid off his accusers. since then, numerous prominent figures â€” from actors and comedians to lawmakers and scientists â€” have been held accountable for sexual #violence and #abuse, and the #metoo movement has sparked increased awareness about these issues.
.
.
following the weinstein scandal, researchers from #harvard medical school and uc #sandiego took a look at google #search rates for sexual harassment and sexual assault before and after milano's #metoo tweet. to start, the researchers examined trends in these searches from jan. 1, 2004 to oct. 14, 2017 â€” the day before milano first tweeted about #metoo..
.
.
they then used this data to roughly estimate how many times americans would search for these subjects following her tweet, and found that searches for sexual harassment and assault were 86 percent higher than expected from oct. 15, 2017 to june 15, 2018. researchers also discovered a 51 percent increase in searches about preventive training for sexual #harassment and assault, and a 30 percent increase in searches about reporting cases of sexual violence.

according to the #chicago tribune, burke first coined the phrase "me too" in 2006, in order to support women â€” especially black women and women of color â€” who had survived sexual violence. burke has continuously worked to combat sexual violence... read more:

text:
â–ªâ–ªnew review!â–ªâ–ª
i want to tell a little backstory... before i moved to florida earlier this year, i lived in a small community in southern california. it is on that community's facebook page that i "met" the beautiful, talented author, erin lockwood. she had posted about her newest book, and i ended up having a conversation with her through messenger & then subsequently inviting her to join #spiveysğŸ“šclub. i had never heard of her or her work before, but i was definitely intrigued! by the end of the conversation, erin offered me a free kindle copy of her book in exchange for an honest review. erin is humble, honest and kind. below is a summary of the review i sent to her in messenger & am now adding to goodreads! for those of you who enjoy reading the synopsis, swipe right for the @goodreads blurb. ğŸ¤“
â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢
how interesting the timing of this book is! this one was published in january 2018, right in the midst of the #metoo & #timesup movements, making it such an unfortunately relevant topic right now, and one that is long overdue really. the book took a little while for me to get into. i found the characters a little difficult to relate to in the beginning, perhaps because of my age in contrast to theirs, but by the 100th page i was pretty invested. 
by the second half, i could feel things that the characters were feeling and i cared about how it effected them. from reading the blurb the readers knows what's coming, and it's almost like as we got closer to it you are holding your breath wondering if it's going to be this time or when it's going to happen. it's that feeling of dread that you know what's coming. and i'm sure that's how kessia felt too.
the assault itself was some of the best writing i've read in this genre. it was passionate, exciting writing and i teared up while reading it, which is not something i've done often. there is a twist at the end that i really enjoyed and wasn't expecting in this book.
it wasn't an easy read because of the subject matter, but it wasn't overly violent or dark, had a perfect ending, and it was a quick read for me. 
i also encourage anyone who reads this one to read the open letter the author has included at the end. ğŸ’›

text:
so, i wasn't going to post this. i made this on wednesday and have been sitting on it because its nerve wracking. whenever i make my videos it is because i believe i'm being guided to. i was guided to make this, but this video is different. this isn't a typical #maddythehippie video. i'm not sharing the full extent what has happened because the words themselves can be triggering to some people.
but all over my feed i have been seeing things about rkelly or things related to the topic. so i wanted to speak my truth. 
i'd like to state that this particular topic is very difficult to talk about because it opens wounds.  i have been physically and verbally harassed within the last 3 months. one by the man at work, and one by someone i considered to be a friend in my life, who i thought i was safe with. 
i now understand what it's like to be in vulnerable place and not know what actions to take in the moment. to be frozen.  i'm thankful for myself and being able to stand up. most people who have known me know that i have had anxiety for a good chunk of my life. i've always been someone to internalize things people say to me and i hold onto them.
when this happened, a warrior came out. it took a while to really sit with this warrior in me and claim her though. it isn't something i'm used to but i'm learning to love it. 
people take advantage of things they believe they have power over. my point behind this is to state that i am the power and i get to choose to stay in that. 
i'm not sharing because i want pity or people to feel sorry for me. i'm sharing because this is a topic that is very important and it is getting a bad name because there are false accusations being televised like they are happening more than the actual thing. 
there is good and bad to everything in life. there is an extreme to every religion and movement. but i also believe the more people choose to speak their truth, the more the truth comes out. so, #metoo. 
i have taken action on my end and have spoken to who i need. i am powerful and strong, and so are you. you're not alone. i love you.

text: why did i decide to pursue a career in law, specifically the bar? (trigger warning: se/ual harassment)  answer: i did not know my rights- meaning i was unaware of the concept that â€œno one asks for it unless they consentâ€! i am sick and tired of people saying things like â€œdid you see her clothes? she was definitely asking for itâ€ or something like â€œshe didnâ€™t say noâ€ etc. well- after many years of hearing such statements, and after  hearing the world â€œslutâ€ thrown around since i was 15, and literally allowing my name to be dragged through the mud i decided to go to law school to make sure i could fight for myself and fight for many many other people. im pretty sure there are no effective regulations in place in karachi relating to sexual harassment and bullying in schools. when i saw the #timesup movement i was honestly overjoyed.  anyway- i went to a private school and they were easy to blame so many girls for ill mannered and sexually frustrated 16 year old boys (yuck). our principle is seen as a â€œrevolutionaryâ€ but the side i have seen of him left me shocked. he had the audacity to blame young girls for the behaviour of boys who touched them in class (feeling chest area, back, smacking their bum while they were left teary eyed and embarrassed), pulled their bra straps in class and what not. so let me educate you all on consent. legally valid consent is when â€œa person agrees by choice and has the freedom and capacity to make that decisionâ€(section 74 sexual offences act 2003)- so no one is asking for it. if a girl says yes and has capacity to say yes then go ahead do whatever you guys want. however, if a girl/boy consents but: only because s/he is fearful of you, youâ€™ve threatened her/him, you are in a position of power and you force her/him to consent, the person is drunk/drugged or too young to consent there is no valid consent. #consentis #nomeansno #nogreyarea #sexualharrassment #raiseawareness #stopslutshaming #blametheperpetrators #timesup #protectourpeople #educateourpeople #lawschool #barstudent #lincolnsinn #honourablesocietyoflincolnsinn #fightingforeveryonesrights #dontevertouchme #metoo #sexualoffence #c.a.sschoolkarachi

text: i wanted to say this. because i get inboxes etc with "you don't know how bad it is ...". no. i'm not in your shoes. but i've been in mine. more than i have ever posted or ever will. i know the nights of doubt gnawing at you. people snearing at you, condemning you for things that aren't even your doing. i know much. i hear the pain people speak with and i wish i had the magic wand that would allow me to fix it all. but i-can- tell you..you will make it. i never believed i would. there are a couple of people on here who know the truth of that. people that saw, physically, what i was/am going through. please know, you have it in your hands...in your heart and soul to make it!! look in the mirror and decide you will not let it beat you! slowly, surely, grab your life and person back!! i believe in you!! please..believe in yourself!!ğŸ’— #boundaries #nocontact #redflags #narcissist #narcissisticabuse #narcissism #metoo #abuse #crazymaking #traumabonding #emotionalabuse #toxicrelationships #survivor #gaslighting #toxicpeopleÂ  #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolence #believewomen #ifmywoundswerevisible #dontlookback #narcissisticabusesurvivor #pagansofinstagram #power #witchesofinstagram #power #pagansofinstagram #witchesofinstagram

text:
iâ€™m a strong believer in validating the humanity of all who suffer.  i reluctantly watched the documentary and almost wanted to dust off my old text books!  watching and hearing these scary stories may leave some wanting to search for answers and point fingers at the victims, family, friends, etc.  the reality is every person in that documentary at baseline was manipulated and entangled in a web of codependency either before r. kelly or after him.  the #survivingrkelly documentary really shows you how pervasive sexual abuse, digital abuse ( when you are forced to perform sexual acts against your will while being recorded) , sex trafficking, and domestic violence can get.  if you never understood how those forms of violence, the layers of psychological manipulation, power, control, abuse, and grooming in sex crimes work this documentary lays it all out there for you. 
lastly be aware of when you have ignored or repressed your own personal experiences with abuse and seek professional help without condemning others.  shame is the fuel to keep the silence of victim oppression going.  shame itâ€™s everything negative itâ€™s not supportive.  no one deserves to be manipulated and sexually exploited.  no family deserves it either.  #stoptheshame #beapartofthesolution not the problem.

text:
this quote will eventually be on my body forever. it's something i often forget.

the things i've been through don't make me weaker. they make me stronger. i've grown from them and continue to grow as a person. 
the pictures show the difference from jan 2018 to jan 2019. the first picture was taken a week after i was raped. my mental health was shattered and everything i believed about myself was so skewed.

now, i'm in a healthy loving relationship, healing from all the bad things i've lived through.

i'm proud of myself.

text:
â€œwatching the lifetime documentary â€œsurviving r. kelly,â€ executive produced by dream hampton, left me feeling unwashed. i wanted to soak my brain in a tub of hot soapy water with a dab of bleach. my mind was swirling, and i was chasing my thoughts with a butterfly net. in the three-night series, accusers, former employees, journalists and critics lead us into a painfully messy pandoraâ€™s box of abuse orchestrated by kelly and his organized crime family of yes men and do-boys. 
the revelations serve as yet another numbing example of how many of us survive and thrive in oppression â€“ both victimizer and victim. we emerge from the deepest and darkest environments jaded and desensitized by the normalized atrocities we encounter on a too consistent basis. the mish-mash of social media reactions to the decades of allegations is a candid illustration of the divided and varied nature in which we process trauma. by the time i had soldiered through the final episode, i had decided that we helped to create this monster. â€œ - @iamjames_terry 
read more of rachel james-terry, writer phenomenal piece on blackwithnochaser.com

text:
if you have not watched #survivingrkelly yet it may be triggering to sexual assault survivors so watch with caution. r kelly is the perfect example of toxic masculinity and how his traumas have escalated into becoming a predator. in my last post i discuss how toxic masculinity should be a priority, but definitely not in the place of the victims they cause. once they have committed criminal action, they need to be brought to justice. male mental health going undiagnosed, or untreated has major consequences on both women and men. i hope if he ever is brought to court he does not use his past as an excuse for his behaviors. he knew what he was doing was wrong, he tried to cover it up, but #timesup #muterkelly and any other person in power like him who will be exposed in 2019. pray for the #survivors and those still being victimized today.

#blackisbeautiful #blacklivesmatter #blackgirlslivesmatter #rkelly @lifetimetv #sexualassualt #violenceagainstwomen #violenceagainstmen #metoo

text:
trencadÃ­s mosaic tiles covering antoni gaudÃ­â€™s work
.
because we sometimes have to break before we can be whole again.
.
.
â€”â€”â€”
.
.
probably a little too late for a new year recollection post;
2018 saw me survive being:
.
- raped, more than once, by someone that i trusted;
- cheated of my goodwill (and also money) multiple times;
- gaslighted into thinking that i was the one at fault;
- confronted with and experiencing near-death in at least one near-successful suicide attempt;
- dragged through a frivolous lawsuit that attempted to extract even more money from me.
.
.
on new yearâ€™s eve, i spoke rather despondently to a friend about how nothing seems to have gone right for me in 2018.
and that, quite frankly, after a year of being tossed and kicked around, instead of looking hopefully to a new year ahead, i feel like i barely have the strength to make it past the starting line let along finish it.
.
it was at this moment that i remembered the mosaic in gaudÃ­â€™s modernist work.
.
unlike the whole ceramic tiles that were used in preceding art nouveau architecture, gaudÃ­ used trencadÃ­s mosaic â€” which essentially comprises of nonuniformed broken** ceramic / chinaware / glass shards â€” in his work.
.
because breaking the pieces into irregular shapes was the only way he could cover and decorate the irregular curved surfaces of his designs;
and it was also a way for him to reuse old / waste material in his work.
.
it was unconventional technique for his time.
but looking at the walls of gaudÃ­â€™s modernist buildings, all one can see now is absolute undeniable beauty.
.
so yes, 2018 was a broken year for me.
maybe i was broken in the process as well.
and maybe i am still broken.
.
but maybe this is the only way to fit myself back beautifully into the unconventional yet fluid path ahead of me.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: so i stayed up until 2am glued to the tv watching the whole series and was in shock when it ended. i literally could not sleep after that, tossing & turning all night thinking what if it were my daughter. no one can deny this man is a musical genius and legend but on flip side no one can also deny this man is a sexual predator!! before watching it i thought to myself this couldn't be me cuz i'm bringing the whole eastside of midland(shoutout) to r.kelly front door to handle business and get my baby!!! after watching this i realized some of these parents took the extra precautions & did all they could yet still this man has been untouchable. i teach a curriculum, positive action, in schools and it teaches students how to love themselves, values, morals, how to encourage themselves even when others may not be. you will be surprised how many schools still have not let me in to teach students, only in 4 schools out of the 20 something elementarys we have. one thing i tell my students is that if you don't believe or stand for something then you will fall for anything. as mothers, tias, grandmothers, sisters, etc. we have to make our girls aware of what is out there. we need to encourage them to be confident and secure in themselves while also encouraging them to be women warriors. have those open and real conversations about men, dating, the workplace, school and all the things young girls now days may encounter. #survivingrkelly #metoo #muterkelly #eachoneteachone #reallyshookme #heneedstobelockedup

a sky swirling snow globe

thoughts mirroring as glitter shaken into chaos, floating gently to the bottom when the vibration tires. 
shocked, then settled when the vortex calms, no-thing blooms in silent linear minutes, stacking until the whole is absorbed... kerrr-thunk...is the sound as the door shuts.

i meet an australian surfer, near sundown when the sky is blazing orange from toxic pollution. she insists itâ€™s the salt from the sea making the skyâ€™s hues burn. i laugh at her optimism.

we talk about everything, and anything flows into something, seamlessly.

when i tell her about the experience iâ€™ve had as a body housing a mind, she says she understands, completely. she explains the first thing about abusive relationships is you have to see them, in yourself. â€œeveryone has it, to a point. when youâ€™re in an abusive environment, you adapt. you habituate. the sad thing is if you put a miserable person in with a group of five, aggressively happy people, theyâ€™ll bring the sad one up to their level.â€ â€œthat is sad,â€ i say.

text:
....and my manuscript is done. finally. after what has literally been years , iâ€™m done recalling and writing the story of my life. (until now) those that know me personally know how long itâ€™s been. how many re-writes and pauses i had to take because the grief was overwhelming at moments. but my baby is done. .
.
for â€œa million mondaysâ€i was stuck trying to move on but unable. i was stuck in pity, non motivated and not sure if iâ€™d ever truly be free. but finally i made it to tuesday which means i made it through all of the things that i wasnâ€™t sure i would. im both proud, exhausted and excited. and even though iâ€™m a pretty transparent person, there are parts of my story that are heartbreaking and iâ€™m bracing myself for the impact that the raw truth is going to have on my life. .
.
in the wake of the r. kelley documentary and the #metoo movement there are countless other women, just like me, who are forced to live their lives with the pieces of their pasts that are littered with sexual abuse and sexual violence. there is so â€œgold â­ï¸ starâ€ for speaking up about it. you get sympathy (if youâ€™re lucky or known) but the truth is â€”we go back to lives that are almost impossible to thrive in â€”yet we must. yet we must move forward. yet we prevail. yet we endure and remain the silent superheroâ€™s who are not only facing injustice, poverty, mental struggles but also the results of sexual violence as children. our voices will be heard, even if iâ€™m standing alone.
